d?'Teabing hobbled over. 'You were rescued by a knight brandishing an Excalibur made by Acme Orthopedic.\n\n- Dan Brown, The Da Vinci Code\n|\nWhoever count his blessings, shall be content.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nOn the road to wisdom, behave like a raven and observe everything carefully!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nSomeone who dreams cannot be forced to stop—there are no limitations to dreams, because we do not own dreams, dreams are from God.\n\n- Christina Westover, Poisoning Sylvie\n|\nJust remember this, my girl, when you look up in the sky you can see the stars and still not see the light.\n\n- Jack\n|\nHer short blond hair shifted in the wind, and she appeared the very definition of peace and comfort. Like she belonged in the world that had existed before everything was scorched.\n\n- James Dashner, The Kill Order\n|\nAbide not with dualism,Carefully avoid pursuing it;As soon as you have right and wrong,Confusion ensues, and Mind is lost. (172)\n\n- Edward Conze, Buddhist Scriptures\n|\nThe more we surrender to what cannot be, the better we control what can be.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nA true prayer is an inventory of needs, a catalog of necessities, an exposure of secret wounds, a revelation of hidden poverty.\n\n- Charles\n|\nKitten, your hands are heaven and your eyes are my home.\n\n- Jeaniene Frost, This Side of the Grave\n|\nIn order for us to learn to love, first ourselves and the others, we must accept Jesus’ love for us in the deepest parts of our hearts.\n\n- Sara Dormon, If You're a Christian and Everyone Likes You... Something's Wrong\n|\nJenifer always taught me that starting a job was one thing―—and admirable―—but that following through and completing―—well, that’s where the bravery is.\n\n- Valerie Estess, Tales from the Bed\n|\nOh, child, my child, if only you realized who you truly are.\n\n- Toni Sorenson, The Great Brain Cleanse\n|\nThose who fear the imagination condemn it: something childish, they say, something monsterish, misbegotten. Not all of us dream awake. But